CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 3, 1957, pg. A7, reads: "Runners-Up - Baby Karen Jean Coles, left, in the arms of her mother, Mrs. Kathleen Coles seems content with second place in Wesley Center Church's baby contest. Third-place winner, little Denise Anne Turner, held by her grandmother, Mrs. Vestula Youngblood, seems to register surprise. Other contestants were Donna Rena Dominisk, Lois Jean Beasley and Jean Renec Fowler. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Kathleen Coles holding baby daughter Karen Jean Coles and Vestula Youngblood holding baby granddaughter Denise Anne Turner at Wesley Center AME Zion Church baby contest
